    /*

    More info here: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/getstarted/keybindings

    Pending issues: #59083, #59084

    Todo: 
        Find/Replace
        Debug
        Text edition
        auto-complete & code-navigation

    ----------------------------------------------------------

    General MAJOR-KEY meanings - Used with Meta (Super) key:
     · S:   Sidebar
     · E:   Editor
     · W:   Explorer
     · F:   Find
     · D:   Debug
     · G:   Panel
     · R:   Problems view
     · T:   Terminal

    General MINOR-KEY meanings:
     · A:   Focus/View/Toggle
     · X:   Split
     · W:   Next/other
     · E:   Expand/Contract
     · F:   File (open, show...)
     · N:   New/Create
     · D:   Close

    ----------------------------------------------------------

    Focus on views:
     · Meta+S A         : Focus sidebar (XXX toggle not suported yet, focus needed: issue #59084)
     · Meta+W A         : Toggle focus between editor and file explorer
     · Meta+E A         : Focus active editor (from anywhere)
     · Meta+R A         : Focus on problems view (XXX toggle not suported yet, focus needed: issue #59084)
     · Meta+T A         : Toggle focus between editor and terminal
     · Ctrl+Shift+F      : Toggle focus to find/replace
     · Ctrl+Shift+D      : Toggle focus to Debugger
    
    Sidebar (Meta+S):
     · Meta+S A         : Focus sidebar (XXX toggle not suported yet, focus needed: issue #59084)
     · Meta+S E         : Expand/collapse Sidebar

    File explorer (Meta+W):
     · Meta+W A         : Focus on file explorer (toggle)
     · Meta+W C         : New file
     · Meta+W Meta+C    : New folder
     · Meta+W F         : Reveal current file in file explorer (if in workspace)
     · Meta+W D         : Hide file explorer
     · Enter            : File: open, Folder: expand/collapse
     · Ctrl+Enter       : Open to side

    Editor (Meta+E):
     · Meta+E A         : Focus active editor (from anywhere)
     · Ctrl+P           : Quick open file...
     · Ctrl+W           : Close active file window
     · Ctrl+K Ctrl+W    : Close all open files
     · Meta+E X         : Split editor horizontally
     · Meta+E Meta+X    : Split editor vertically
     · Alt+1-9          : Focus file at position 1-9 (same group)
     · Ctrl+Tab         : Focus editor on next file (same group)
     · Ctrl+Alt+Tab     : Focus next editor group

    Panel (Meta+G):
     · Meta+G D         : Hide Panel

    Problems view (Meta+R):
     · Meta+R A         : Focus on problems view (XXX toggle not suported yet, focus needed: issue #59084)
     · Enter            : Open problem in editor
     · Ctrl+Enter       : Open problem in new side editor
     · Meta+R D         : Hide problems view ( XXX not supported yet: issue #59083)

    Terminal (Meta+T):
     · Meta+T A         : Toggle focus between editor and terminal
     · Meta+T Meta+A    : Add new terminal (another window) and focus
     · Meta+T X         : Split terminal (add a pane and focus)
     · Meta+T W         : Switch focus to next terminal pane
     · Meta+T Meta+W    : Switch focus to next terminal window
     · Meta+T E         : Toggle terminal Expand/collapse
     · Meta+T F         : Open new terminal in location of current file
     · Meta+T D         : Hide terminal view
     · Terminal text edition:
         · Ctrl+Shift+C : Copy (linux terminal)
         · Ctrl+Shift+V : Paste (linux terminal)
         · Ctrl+D       : Kill

    Compiling and Debugging:
     · F5:              : Execute launch configuration and debug
     · Shift+F5          : Stop debugging execution
     · Ctrl+Shift+B      : Run default build task
     · Ctrl+Shift+Alt+B  : Run non-default task (choose)

    BreadCrumbs:
     · Ctrl+Shift+I:    : Shows BreadCrumbs view of current file

    ----------------------------------------------------------

    Editor :: Multiple Cursors:
     · Ctrl+Shift+Up/Down   : Add cursor on next/previous line
     · Alt+Click            : Add cursor on mouse click

    Editor :: Text Selection:
     · Ctrl+I                   : Select current line
     · Shift+Left/Right          : Select next/previous char
     · Ctrl+Shift+Left/Right     : Select next/previous word
     · Ctrl+Shift+Alt+Left/Right : Select next/previous sub-word
     · Shift+Up/Down             : Select/deselect next/previous line
     · Ctrl+Shift+Up/Down        : Add next/previous line to selection
     · Ctrl+D                   : Select current word, or select next word occurrence
     · Ctrl+U                   : Soft undo: deselect last selection added with Ctrl+D
     · Ctrl+Shift+L              : Select all occurrences of currently selected text
     · Alt+Up/Down              : Move selected text up/down

    Editor :: Navigation:
     · Ctrl+L                   : Go to Line

    Cancel, leave... (similar to Escape key, anywhere):
     · Ctrl+G           : Leave, cancel, exit... (depends on context)

    ---------------------------------------------------------- 
    
    */

